1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,080
I'll see you tomorrow, Hyeji.

2
00:00:04,360 --> 00:00:06,660
Can I go too?

3
00:00:09,580 --> 00:00:11,500
<i> [The Witch Store]</i>

4
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:17,680
<i> [Episode 4] 
 [Meeting the One I Never Want to Lose to]</i>

5
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,880
<i> Why did he come here?</i>

6
00:00:21,880 --> 00:00:24,360
You are Han Yuho, right?

7
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:26,190
Do you know me?

8
00:00:26,190 --> 00:00:28,170
<i>[Han Yuho]</i>

9
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,900
Right...

10
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:32,880
Is this place newly opened?

11
00:00:32,880 --> 00:00:35,660
If you've never seen this place, it may be newly opened.

12
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:38,559
What do you want? We have everything.

13
00:00:38,559 --> 00:00:41,200
Um... I want hot chocolate latte.

14
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:42,880
We don't have that.

15
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:44,540
It's on the menu.

16
00:00:44,540 --> 00:00:49,000
I just wrote it for fun. And this is not a cafe.

17
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,740
- Sorry. 
 - Wait.

18
00:00:52,740 --> 00:00:54,800
Take a look around first.

19
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:58,320
There are new products.

20
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:08,240
<i> What scam is she trying to run now?</i>

21
00:01:09,460 --> 00:01:10,900
How about something like this?

22
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:13,760
You can jump three times higher with these.

23
00:01:13,760 --> 00:01:18,880
You could jump high enough to go through the roof.

24
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:21,400
How much is it?

25
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:23,140
200 million won?

26
00:01:23,140 --> 00:01:25,560
I just bought a pair of shoes not too long ago.

27
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:28,280
Really? That's unfortunate.

28
00:01:30,680 --> 00:01:32,080
How about this?

29
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:37,100
This is a magical product that makes your skin glow just like the skin that you've had in your 20s.

30
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:40,660
If you buy it, I'll give you 50% discount.

31
00:01:40,660 --> 00:01:44,039
How about it? You want it, right?

32
00:01:44,039 --> 00:01:47,780
Sorry, but I'm 18.

33
00:01:48,660 --> 00:01:53,540
Oh, I thought so. Your skin is so nice.

34
00:01:57,020 --> 00:01:58,940
How about this one, then?

35
00:01:58,940 --> 00:02:01,400
Oh? I saw this candy before.

36
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:05,720
Oh! Your memory is remarkable.

37
00:02:07,180 --> 00:02:09,900
<i> Not that one!</i>

38
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:11,720
Ignore that.

39
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:14,440
That's just my cat being noisy.

40
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:19,160
Where did that candy go?

41
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:22,580
Candy? What candy?

42
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:28,600
What is this place?

43
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:32,480
It's the store that can make your wish come true.

44
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,980
Wish?

45
00:02:33,980 --> 00:02:35,320
Yeah.

46
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:39,800
So, tell me what you really want.

47
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:42,480
I don't want anything.

48
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:47,340
I bet you need this.

49
00:02:48,140 --> 00:02:49,720
What is this?

50
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:50,980
A judo belt.

51
00:02:50,980 --> 00:02:55,520
If you wear this, you can definitely beat anyone.

52
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:59,000
Wait... How could it...?

53
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,880
Why? You don't need it?

54
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:03,160
How much is this?

55
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:05,820
As it's your first time here, I'll give it to you for free.

56
00:03:05,820 --> 00:03:08,260
Next time, bring your friend.

57
00:03:08,260 --> 00:03:11,160
Really? Thank you.

58
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:13,600
Bye.

59
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,260
Bye.

60
00:03:15,260 --> 00:03:17,560
Come back with your friend next time.

61
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:22,660
How did he come here?

62
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:24,700
He must have needed to come here.

63
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:29,380
Ah! I'm going to charge you for the product that he took. It'll be deducted from your salary.

64
00:03:29,380 --> 00:03:32,300
You don't pay me anyways.

65
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:38,240
<i> Does this really work?</i>

66
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,540
Hi.

67
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:44,300
- Hey, Hyeongsuk. 
 - Yeah?

68
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:47,140
- Are you busy these days? 
 - Why?

69
00:03:47,140 --> 00:03:48,740
Just...

70
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:52,120
Can you help me practice judo?

71
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:55,300
Sorry. I'm busy.

72
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:57,280
Hey...

73
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:59,420
Help me.

74
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:01,760
Why do you want to practice judo all of a sudden?

75
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:05,280
Are you really going to fight Yoon Sungwoo?

76
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:08,120
No. I just haven't done it for a while.

77
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:10,840
You will never defeat him. He's in the judo club.

78
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:12,700
Please. Help me.

79
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:15,740
I have never done judo. How am I going to help you?

80
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:17,440
You do boxing.

81
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:20,140
Boxing and judo are not the same.

82
00:04:20,140 --> 00:04:22,560
Hyeongsuk, please.

83
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:24,519
- I can't. 
 - Help me.

84
00:04:24,519 --> 00:04:25,900
No, I don't want to.

85
00:04:25,900 --> 00:04:28,740
- Hey. 
 - I don't know.

86
00:04:28,740 --> 00:04:32,120
You need to have strength to do any sports.

87
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,180
Of course.

88
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:36,800
From today on, you'll run ten laps during lunchtime.

89
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:39,360
Okay, ten laps.

90
00:04:39,940 --> 00:04:42,380
What are you doing? Start running.

91
00:04:47,420 --> 00:04:49,120
He's torturing himself.

92
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:51,040
Just use the one you got yesterday.

93
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,780
Isn't it defected like the candy last time?

94
00:04:53,780 --> 00:04:56,140
What are you talking about? That was an unfinished product.

95
00:04:56,140 --> 00:04:58,040
And it was effective anyways.

96
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:00,360
Well, yeah...

97
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:04,080
But that's cheating. Would he really use it?

98
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:08,400
I don't know. We'll have to wait and see.

99
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:12,460
Wow. They run so well.

100
00:05:12,460 --> 00:05:15,319
- Let's run together. 
 - No thank you.

101
00:05:18,980 --> 00:05:20,420
How many laps do we have left?

102
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:22,600
We just ran one lap.

103
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,860
Don't you think running ten laps is too much?

104
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:26,600
We also have to study.

105
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,780
When did we study during lunch time?

106
00:05:28,780 --> 00:05:31,560
It's bad for our health if we run right after we eat.

107
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,900
Then don't do it.

108
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:34,180
No, no.

109
00:05:34,180 --> 00:05:37,200
It feels good to run.

110
00:05:38,260 --> 00:05:41,400
I like everything about school except for classes.

111
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:43,260
You've adapted well.

112
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:45,120
Let's go to work now.

113
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:47,960
You have two months left. Keep your promise.

114
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:50,880
No. It's two months and one day.

115
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:53,260
Why did you add one more day?

116
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:54,920
Hyeji.

117
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,820
Do you have time tomorrow?

118
00:05:57,820 --> 00:05:59,799
Tomorrow? Why?

119
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:04,520
We have judo practice match at school tomorrow. If you have time, come and watch.

120
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:08,860
I want to go, but I have to go to my part-time job tomorrow.

121
00:06:08,860 --> 00:06:11,540
Really? That's a shame.

122
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:15,340
Did I not tell you that your boss told you to take a day off tomorrow?

123
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:16,420
Really?

124
00:06:16,420 --> 00:06:18,520
Then, I'll go. What time is it tomorrow?

125
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:20,896
2 pm. Come to the school gym.

126
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,460
Can I go as well?

127
00:06:22,460 --> 00:06:25,720
Sure. I'll see you tomorrow, Hyeji.

128
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:29,260
Can I go too?

129
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:39,840
This is nice.

130
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:42,860
My trainer would kill me if he knew that I came here.

131
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:44,420
Then you should be fine as long as you don't get caught.

132
00:06:44,420 --> 00:06:46,540
And it's not the time to build strength.

133
00:06:46,540 --> 00:06:47,800
It's all about the actual fight.

134
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:49,560
You've said that you can't remember how to do judo.

135
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:52,780
Don't worry. I have something prepared.

136
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,700
You prepared this?

137
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:06,800
You are going to win with this?

138
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:11,280
As we don't have a lot of time, let's just focus on one of the techniques from here.

139
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:16,460
Okay, then let's do this one. Holding the opponent down.

140
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:20,960
Making the opponent still by choking or twisting.

141
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:23,220
Isn't it too harsh?

142
00:07:23,220 --> 00:07:25,600
What about this one then. Home thrust.

143
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:30,680
Dominating the match by temporarily stopping the physical function of the opponent.

144
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:31,640
That's also...

145
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:34,080
Then, what do you want?

146
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:35,380
What about this?

147
00:07:35,380 --> 00:07:39,100
This is all about judo. Shoulder throw.

148
00:07:48,820 --> 00:07:50,760
Are you kidding me?

149
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:51,770
Why?

150
00:07:51,770 --> 00:07:53,850
What is this?

151
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:58,060
Hyeongsuk, you can't dodge it.

152
00:07:58,060 --> 00:08:00,240
Just do it.

153
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,980
I'm going now!

154
00:08:03,540 --> 00:08:05,740
Hey! Loosen up!

155
00:08:05,740 --> 00:08:09,480
I'm not doing anything. You need to use more force.

156
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:14,660
Is this not it? But, the posture is correct, right?

157
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:15,720
Let's take turns.

158
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:19,559
What's the problem here? This will never...

159
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:21,920
Woah.

160
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,520
Are you okay?

161
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:25,260
Oh, it works.

162
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:28,940
How could you not even do the throw once?

163
00:08:28,940 --> 00:08:32,060
Let's do it one more time. I think I'm getting it.

164
00:08:32,060 --> 00:08:35,500
Why did you say that you are going to see the practice match tomorrow?

165
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,220
I don't know.

166
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:40,340
Let's go. I'm tired.

167
00:08:40,340 --> 00:08:41,960
Hey.

168
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:56,860
What is that?

169
00:08:56,860 --> 00:08:59,340
It's to show my resolution. Come here.

170
00:08:59,340 --> 00:09:01,000
It won't work.

171
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,780
I'll bet fifty thousand won that...

172
00:09:03,780 --> 00:09:07,520
♫ <i> Dozens of times a day </i> ♫

173
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:09,160
It works.

174
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:15,080
<i> [Victory for the Judo Belt]</i>

175
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:19,100
♫ <i> Honestly, I had no idea this kind of thing </i> ♫

176
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:23,390
♫ <i> Would happen to me </i> ♫

177
00:09:23,390 --> 00:09:28,440
♫ <i> Like the sound of a bell in my mind </i> ♫

178
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:31,770
♫ <i> I understood what it was </i> ♫

179
00:09:31,770 --> 00:09:36,540
I won.

180
00:09:36,540 --> 00:09:37,800
Do you want to do it again?
